data.description: Welcome to your dream countryside oasis and automotive enthusiast's paradise! This spacious 4 bedroom (additional 1 room flex space currently being used as an office), 2 bath home is nestled on a sprawling 1-acre lot, offering plenty of room to spread out and enjoy the great outdoors. This home features a family room as you walk into the front door being overlooked by the eat in kitchen. Large master bath is perfect to end your long day by soaking in the oversized garden tub. Home contains hardwood flooring throughout. The property features a large detached shop that's already set up for restoring cars, making it a car lover's dream. Say goodbye to pesky HOA rules and fees, as this property has none! The HEATED, COOLED AND INSULATED workshop provides ample space for all your tools, and projects, perfect for indulging your automotive hobbies. After a day of tinkering in the shop, relax and unwind on the covered back porch while enjoying the serene views of your own private slice of paradise. Whether you're a nature lover, hobbyist, or just looking for a peaceful retreat with space for your automotive projects, this home is a rare gem that won't last long. Don't miss out on the opportunity to make it yours! Home was purchased as a mobile home and titles retired. Home is now considered real estate and can hold $0 Down USDA | VA loan, or FHA | Conventional loan. Due to the complexity of financing a converted mobile home, preferred lender is Tony Rodarte at Lux Financial and preferred closing atty is Lueder, Larkin & Hunter.
